        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_GetProgress",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve progress information related to billing processes for accounts. It operates in two modes: a consolidated report mode when no specific account number is provided, and a detailed mode when an account number and billing period are specified. The procedure queries data from two tables, "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Batch.FileStep",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Batch.Step",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", to determine the status of various steps in the billing process."
        }
      ]
    },
